SEOON D PROLOGUE.

The interest of the second prologue consists in its being a trial scene, wherein two characters are brought upon the stage one after the other and tried before Ignoramus and his clerk Dulman. The first to be examined and sentenced is the same Davus Dromo, alias Messe Davy, who was ridiculed by the use of the hobby·horse in the first prologue. The second person to appear before the mock·tribunal was a character representing the famous German scholar, and champion of the Pope, Gaspar SchioppiUS, who had not only written against Protestants in all Europe, but had also for various reasons satirized King J ames without mercy.
